title: Senior Solution Engineer - REMOTE or Bay Area
description:
Senior Solution Engineer

Employment Status: Full-Time

Job Location: Alameda CA. Working remotely is an option with some travel.

APPLY HERE - https://recruiting2.ultipro.com/TEL1006/JobBoard/2fcbb6f4-e717-17cb-9327-3dd87a55b08d/OpportunityDetail?opportunityId=57295fa5-8bcf-46e2-9b1b-f73360dd5c12

Who you'll work with?
Telecare is a rapidly growing mental health care company dedicated to making a difference for our clients, the community, and our employees. We offer an array of mental health services to adults with serious mental illnesses. We specialize in innovative, outcomes-driven services for high-risk individuals with complex needs. To learn more about Telecare, visit us at https://www.telecarecorp.com/at-a-glance

You will be an integral part of Telecare's Special Projects team. We are a fun, hardworking collaborative team that believes in modern development practices and team collaboration. We have a passion for building strategies, solutions, and creative products to help solve complex and interesting business problems and make a direct difference in how our doctors, clinicians, and staff provide care and support to thousands of patients daily.

What you'll do:
Design & build business solutions, applications & tools using web technologies, APIs, integrations, and automation.
Leverage your skills across the full stack of web technology, frontend, API, backend.
Identify areas of technical debt and influence roadmap plans with smart solutions.
Contribute to the architecture and design of new and current systems

What You Should Have:
Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering or equivalent experience
4+ years of professional software development experience
2+ Hands-on experience in Microsoft C# / ASP.NET stack, preferably .Net Core and/or .NET 5+
Proficiency in one or more object-oriented programming languages and practices
Strong system and data analysis skills
Proven success leading projects from start to finish with the ability to effectively articulate technical challenges and solutions.

What Will Set You Apart?
Full-stack development experience (DB design, UI/UX design)
Hands-on experience building and consuming REST APIs
Knowledge of Azure, AWS, or similar cloud computing platforms (Azure preferred)
Hands-on experience with data analysis, data integration & ETL, data reporting tools & techniques
Prior experience in the Healthcare industry
EOE AA M/F/V Disability

APPLY HERE - https://recruiting2.ultipro.com/TEL1006/JobBoard/2fcbb6f4-e717-17cb-9327-3dd87a55b08d/OpportunityDetail?opportunityId=57295fa5-8bcf-46e2-9b1b-f73360dd5c12

Keywords: C#, .Net, .Net Core, ASP.Net, MVC, IIS, Azure, SSO, SQL, SQL Server, SSIS, ETL, Qlik, Tableau, Healthcare, Mental health

title: Senior Full-stack Engineer | $140,000 - $180,000 per year
description:
If you're interested in applying for the role, you can check it out here:
https://www.hireart.com/jobs/3506e90b/apply


HireArt is looking for a Senior Full-stack Engineer to help architect and implement features in our Rails back-end and React front-end. 

In this role, you'll also contribute to our R&D effort, working with domain experts to incorporate their knowledge and experience into the web app.

We're open to both fully remote employees based in North America as well as in-person work at our office in New York, NY (once reopened).

Our tech stack includes Rails, React, GraphQL, some Redux, Postgres, Git, and Heroku. Each engineer has ownership over specific product verticals, and we enlist each other's help to get things shipped. We like to have thoughtful group discussions on a range of topics, from software architecture to company strategy. We make sure every voice is heard and every opinion is considered.



If you're interested in applying for the role, you can check it out here:
https://www.hireart.com/jobs/3506e90b/apply


Requirements


5+ years of professional programming experience
3+ years of professional experience with Ruby on Rails (or a similar MVC framework)
Are comfortable in at least one modern Javascript front-end framework (ideally React)
Are interested in the hiring process and are excited about improving it
Are a strong communicator, both synchronously and asynchronously
Are excited about being a part of (and fostering) an engineering culture that embraces collaborative exploration in the pursuit of robust, scalable solutions




Commitment:This is a full-time (40 hours per week) position. We are open to both fully remote employees as well as in-person work at our office in New York, NY (once reopened). The ability to accommodate typical Eastern Standard Time (EST) working hours is preferred.

HireArt values ​​​​diversity and is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We are interested in every qualified candidate in North America. Applicants residing in the United States must be authorized to work in the United States. Unfortunately, we are not able to sponsor visas.

If you're interested in applying for the role, you can check it out here:
https://www.hireart.com/jobs/3506e90b/apply

title: Engineering Manager | $190,000 - $225,000
description:
If you're interested in applying for the role, you can check it out here:
https://www.hireart.com/jobs/6154969e/apply



 HireArt has built the first end-to-end HRIS platform for W2 contingent workforce management, and we’re looking for a hands-on engineering manager with experience in full-stack web development to join a team focused on the employment operations side of our platform.Our ideal candidate is a player-coach: great at managing people and projects, happy supporting and mentoring a team of talented engineers, willing to be hands-on writing code, and eager to manage their own product features.You’ll help solve technical challenges inherent in distilling complex employment operations processes into a seamless, fully-featured, and easy to use platform. You’ll also collaborate with teams across the organization, including Product, Operations, and Account Management, playing a key role in making cross-functional engineering decisions, including creating new features.Day-to-day Responsibilities Lead, support, and guide a  team of engineers to ensure on time deliveryWork closely with product managers and engineers to develop the team’s roadmap Write code, architect solutions, and be a part of code reviews that contribute to the team’s code baseLead and facilitate product manager and software engineers in agile ceremonies and implementing processesRemove roadblocks, identify issues, drive resolutions, and proactively enhance the developer experience to optimize team efficiency 


If you're interested in applying for the role, you can check it out here:
https://www.hireart.com/jobs/6154969e/apply


Requirements

At least 1 year of experience leading a team of engineers  At least 5 years experience as a software engineer Experience with modern JavaScript frameworks  Experience writing production software with Ruby  Experience building, shipping and maintaining web applications that are reliable, testable and maintainable  Ability to summarize technical and complex ideas or solutions  Ability to lead a team in scoping and estimating work across multiple sprints  Strong communication and interpersonal skills  Highly organized with a strong attention to detail  Proven track record of working cross functionally with Engineering, Product, Design and business stakeholders.  BS or BA or equivalent experience.    Nice to Haves:  Experience working within a complex and critical business domain.  Experience with  ReactJSCommitment: This is a remote, permanent, full-time position with HireArt and is open to candidates who are base and authorized to work in U.S. and Canada. Unfortunately, we are not able to sponsor visa or open to corp-to-corp.HireArt values diversity and is an equal opportunity employer, which is why we are interested in every qualified candidate, regardless of their background or how they identify.  Compensation: Our target cash compensation range is $190,000 - $225,000 in New York City & the San Francisco Bay Area and $160,000 - $185,000 in Denver, CO & most other metropolitan areas. Final offer amounts are determined by multiple factors, including experience and level of expertise.HireArt offers equity and a benefits package that includes:  100% employer covered insurance premiums Health, Dental, and Vision insurance for employee, spouse, and childrenLife and disability insuranceWork-from-home stipends, includingWorkspace/home office set upCompany supplied laptop of your choice (Mac or PC)Phone/Internet serviceLunch/SnacksUnlimited PTO and paid holidays


If you're interested in applying for the role, you can check it out here:
https://www.hireart.com/jobs/6154969e/apply



About HireArt
 HireArt is building the first full-stack platform for businesses to source, employ, and manage contract W-2 employees. Our employment platform is the world’s first fully-featured HRIS for the contract W-2 workforce, a massive and growing segment of the labor market. We combine hiring and employment in a single platform, creating a magical experience for businesses: search, interview, make offers, and manage workers, all in one place. Once on board, HireArt provides contract workers with a caring home base that comes with all of the benefits & support associated with permanent employment.  Our goal is to enable businesses to focus on the people who make up their workforce, instead of the tools to manage it. That's why we've developed a transparent and simple to use end-to-end platform that provides contract work opportunities with the security and stability of traditional W-2 employment while still giving businesses the flexibility they need to scale their workforces. 

If you're interested in applying for the role, you can check it out here:
https://www.hireart.com/jobs/6154969e/apply
